parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the airbag is designed to provide critical protection to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Airbag does not deploy in a crash
despite meeting the deployment criteria
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of braking power, and accidents, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
loud noise when applying brakes
jerk and lockup
sudden loss of braking power
and extended stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to stop the vehicle properly
the brake pedal goes to the floor
loud noise when applying brakes
jerk and lockup
and sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, leading to loss of braking power and accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
brake fluid leaks
and sudden loss of braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power booster can cause the brake pedal to be difficult to press, leading to loss of braking power and accidents.
symptoms: The power booster fails
and the cruise control engages automatically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper blade motor can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The windshield wiper blade motor fails intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to bind, lock up, or fail to retract, which can lead to difficulties in putting on or removing the seat belt, and potentially increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt binds up above the bracket
the seat belt folds over and jams
the seat belt does not retract into the housing
the seat belt locks up
the seat belt will not release properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt anchor can cause the seat belt to separate from the door and floor, which can lead to a loss of seat belt functionality and potentially increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The clip that holds the seat belt where it attaches to the door and floor separates.
